Upon its retail release, ''Counter-Strike'' received highly favorable reviews.<ref name="IGN Review">{{Cite web|url = https://www.ign.com/articles/2000/11/23/counter-strike-2|title = Counter-Strike Review|date = November 22, 2000|accessdate = April 1, 2014|website = [[IGN]]|archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20121025152316/http://www.ign.com/articles/2000/11/23/counter-strike-2 |archivedate =October 25, 2012 |url-status =live |last = Wolfe|first = Clayton}}</ref><ref name="GameRankings" /><ref name="Metacritic" /><ref name="GameRev">{{cite web | last = Dodson | first = Joe | url = http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/counter-strike | title = ''Counter-Strike'' Review | date = January 1, 2001 | accessdate = January 29, 2014 | publisher = [[Game Revolution]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202180740/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/counter-strike | archive-date = February 2, 2014 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref name="GameSpot Review">{{Cite web|url = http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/half-life-counter-strike-review/1900-2657769/|title = Half-Life: Counter-Strike Review|accessdate = April 1, 2014|date = November 27, 2000|website = [[GameSpot]]|archivedate =April 1, 2014 |url-status =live |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20140401230830/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/half-life-counter-strike-review/1900-2657769/ |last = Osborne|first = Scott}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'' reported that E-Sports Entertainment [[ESEA League]] started the first professional fantasy e-sports league in 2004 with the game ''Counter-Strike''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/05/magazine/05wwln_consumed.html|title=Double Fantasy |accessdate=March 16, 2014 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date = February 5, 2006|last = Walker|first = Rob|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121025044509/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/05/magazine/05wwln_consumed.html|archivedate = October 25, 2012|url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://